From: m5-linux project
Subject: [PATCH 2/N] midr: Add M4 Pro/Max and M5 CPU MIDR part identifiers

All MIDR_PART_* values below are XXX. They are NOT in the ADT — cpu-impl-reg
holds MMIO base addresses, not MIDR part IDs — so they must come from
`mrs midr_el1` on real hardware. The progression from upstream m1n1 midr.h:

  T6020 (M2 Pro/Max): E=0x34/0x38, P=0x35/0x39
  T8122/T6030/T6031 (M3 / Pro / Max): E=0x42/0x44/0x48, P=0x43/0x45/0x49
  T8132 (M4 base, "Donan"): E=0x52, P=0x53        <- confirmed in upstream
  T8140 (A18 Pro, "Tahiti"): E=0x60, P=0x61       <- confirmed in upstream

Likely (NOT confirmed) for T6040/T6041 (M4 Pro/Max): E=0x54/0x58, P=0x55/0x59,
continuing the 0x5x M4 block. M5 is genuinely uncertain: A18 Pro already
occupies the 0x60/0x61 slot, so M5 base/Pro/Max could land at 0x6x or 0x7x —
do not assume "next after Donan". Confirm on hardware before use.

--- a/src/midr.h
+++ b/src/midr.h
@@ ... (after T8140 entries) ...
+
+/* M4 Pro (T6040) — XXX: mrs midr_el1 on hardware (not in ADT) */
+#define MIDR_PART_T6040_ECORE  0xXX
+#define MIDR_PART_T6040_PCORE  0xXX
+
+/* M4 Max (T6041) — XXX: mrs midr_el1 on hardware (not in ADT) */
+#define MIDR_PART_T6041_ECORE  0xXX
+#define MIDR_PART_T6041_PCORE  0xXX
+
+/* M5 base (T8142) — XXX: mrs midr_el1 on hardware (not in ADT) */
+#define MIDR_PART_T8142_ECORE  0xXX
+#define MIDR_PART_T8142_PCORE  0xXX
+
+/* M5 Pro (T6050) — XXX: mrs midr_el1 on hardware (not in ADT) */
+#define MIDR_PART_T6050_ECORE  0xXX
+#define MIDR_PART_T6050_PCORE  0xXX
+
+/* M5 Max (T6051) — XXX: absent from 25F71; mrs midr_el1 on hardware */
+#define MIDR_PART_T6051_ECORE  0xXX
+#define MIDR_PART_T6051_PCORE  0xXX
